It does to the extent the both, *before* use, are fair marketable items.  That's what they are when they drop.  <br>
A caster would buy a 10k spell just as much as a melee would buy a 10K weapon.  Outside of guild raids, a valuable drop is a valuable drop and should be treated as fair game to all who worked equally hard to earn it.  <br>
<br>
It *is* unfair to casters that they can't sell a spell once they've got an upgrade, but you won't have a melee spending their surplus &quot;feign death&quot; or &quot;evade&quot; money on items like you could have a caster spending their &quot;buff/port/rez.. tips&quot; on spells. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upolaris66.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Polaris66</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/6/02 4:01:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22643.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NBG....</span><hr size=1> Ok, so what about a similar scenario?  Say a lammy drops and me, being a rogue, can't wield it.  However I can use it as a down payment on that +7 Dagger of Instant Whoopass which I most definitely can and will use.  Is it greed to want to upgrade my rusty dagger?<br>
<br>
Now, personally I tend to be the type who's all for giving spell drops to the appropriate class if they're present and rolling otherwise.  But let's face it, NBG is flawed and will always be flawed except in small, tight-knit groups.  Don't expect a pick-up group to understand that just because you can't wield a lammy doesn't mean you can't use it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ustrykninedshiv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stryknine DShiv</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/6/02 4:13:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22643.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NBG....</span><hr size=1> I personally think NBG is a bad idea on any pickup group, because of the obvious reasons mentioned above (being awarded loot without needing to roll, hitting EC 2 days later and making 25k+ profit from it, and returning and doing the same).  Unless there is someone buying a RBG at the zone in for 25k or so, which can then be divided amongst the group, there is no &quot;Equal&quot; way of distributing loot- and we know how often people carry 25k around with them.<br>
<br>
So you have to just do what is the most fair- and the MOST fair way of dealing with any pickup group loot is a system of Open rolling. What I personally use is this: Every item is open rolled, however you can NOT roll on an item if you have already won something- unless you turn in the item you won (if and only if you do WIN the roll on the new item).<br>
<br>
Example: OS Crypt group of 6 people (Wiz, sham, rogue, paladin, cleric, enchanter). <br>
Heiro cloak drops, Shaman wins the random.<br>
DW Helm drops, Shaman is out of the roll, so 5 members roll and the Rogue wins.<br>
Then a JBB drops and the shaman opts to turn in his heiro cloak for a roll on the JBB. Wizard wins the JBB , so SHaman keeps his Heiro cloak. <br>
Then a Copy of Malo drops off the Emporer- EVERYONE opts to turn in the stuff they won to roll for the Scroll (Malo goes for ALOT of plat, at least on bertox).<br>
Rogue wins Malo (yay rogue!), Shaman keeps Heiro  cloak, wizard keeps jbb, DW helm is rerolled on by the ones with No loot yet and the Paladin wins.<br>
Cleric and Enchanter get screwed on loot this time, but maybe they get lucky next time.<br>
<br>
Its not perfect, but its as good as Ive come up with for pickup groups (which I try to avoid anyway). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udaishinzo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dai Shinzo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/6/02 4:52:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22643.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NBG....</span><hr size=1> In a pick up group if the item isn't class specific ( ie spells ) and everyone was there to help then everyone can roll.  90% of the time the melee just sells it anyway.  Which in this case would have happened ( I was there last night when all the bitching took place ).  The cleric did auction it but he asked for good cleric items to replace the ones he was wearing and I say good for him.  Next time make sure when you start group you say that our warrior or so and so gets the RBG etc.  I'm sure you will find none guild groups willing to do that <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udaishinzo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dai Shinzo</A> at: 3/6/02 4:54:14 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unimmbull.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nimmbull</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/6/02 5:04:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22643.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>