<br>
And in my example, I would imagine that the Shaman and the Wizard would swap the JBB for the Heiro cloak right there on the spot.  How is that hoarding loot from anyone? You want to talk about Hoarding? If the shaman won the cloak, then the JBB dropped and he won that, then Malo dropped and he won that as well, who Hoarded What?<br>
<br>
And you want to say &quot;If you want to get gear to upgrade what you already have, go there and get it, don't camp other peoples gear just for cash&quot;.. well, I used to feel that way as well. But guess what- its just not the way things work in EQ.  The place your gear drops is either camped, or takes more than a pickup group to get to, or for some other reason you can't do it.  (And by the way, good luck getting to that easy to kill 60th level emperor, or that JBB, or Heiro cloak without a rogue).<br>
<br>
<br>
No one persons time is more valuable then anyone elses in a pickup group. To tell a person they have no shot at any worthwhile loot, because the &quot;shaman&quot; or the &quot;Enchanter&quot; is going to get preference over someone else, is bullshi%. If you spend your time in that god fosaken area, then you have just as much right as anyone else for a chance at the items. <br>
<br>
The only case where you can't really open roll is for No-Drop items (obviously), in which case the people who would use it roll.<br>
<br>
*Note* This method of loot distribution is for SMALL PICKUP GROUPS where you dont know the majority of the people you are grouped with. I am not (and would never be) in a guild who would open roll on items for people to sell - a guild is all about strengthening the GUILD.<br>
<br>
<br>
Yeah, Im glad you are on Bristlebain as well.<br>
<br>
