<br>
NBG favours the greedy. It favours those people who do nothing but go to the camps that drop their own little class specific items. In a guild setting, I wouldn't tolerate this. I help you with Melee Item A, you help me with Caster Item B. In a group of people I don't know, that responsibility isn't there. I am not going to help you unless you help me in return. It may seem selfish, but that's how this game works. I can't run around in cloth and a fine steel dagger and be effective. I need my int, mana, hp, and resist gear, along with my spells.<br>
<br>
And, who is to say who rolls for what?<br>
<br>
Runebranded Girdles are all/all. Who are you to say that this item isn't for me? Who are you to decide who is more appropriate for whom?<br>
<br>
What about bards? They don't rely on melee much, so obviously they shouldn't roll.<br>
<br>
Paladins and SK's do sucky damage, so they shouldn't roll!<br>
<br>
Rangers don't even do warrior damage, so they shouldn't roll.<br>
<br>
Well, warriors just have to taunt, not actually do damage, so they can't roll.<br>
<br>
Monks can't roll either, because monks really shouldn't depend on gear!<br>
<br>
So, only rogues should roll on RBG's...<br>
<br>
right?<br>
<br>
If you say no to this, then you would really have no basis in saying a caster shouldn't roll.<br>
<br>
Yes, I realize this is only a single item, but the logic applies to everything droppable and re-tradable. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unimmbull.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nimmbull</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/6/02 6:07:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22643.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NBG not enforced</span><hr size=1> Sorry Euriped but I fail to see any logic at all in your post.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
